void Net::RPC::send ( Callback *  cbk,
Upcall *  upk,
long  milli = 0 
)

Send the RPC request This method initiates the rpc protocol by sending the request to be served on the remote node. The callback is notified when the local data of the request may be reused. The upcall is activated on reception of the reply request. The timeout delay, if not 0, is used to signal timeout Errors are detected during sending data by using the error code passed in argument to the callback notification and the error code passed in argument to the upcall. The method is non blocking.

Parameters:
cbk the callback
upk the upcall the should be used to retreive data
milli the timeout in ms

Util::ComFailure::Code Net::RPC::wait (  ) 

Wait acknowledge of the server The return value indicates either no error (OK) and the error code. The most revelent errors are the following, other error code is described in Util::ComFailure class documentation.

Return values:
OK the server has correctly served the request and the return acknowledge is ok
TIMEOUT the delay specify during the invocation of the send is timeout
